interpretation: The "Japanese dolls" card represents the duality of the human experience. Just as dolls are both beautiful and lifeless, we too can feel trapped between two opposing forces. This card reminds us to find balance and harmony within ourselves, even when faced with opposing energies. It may also suggest the need to embrace our inner child and find joy in simple pleasures. Keywords associated with this card include: duality, balance, harmony, inner child, simplicity, beauty, lifelessness.
